Richard P. Lavin



Mr. Richard P. Lavin is Independent Director at Allison Transmission Holdings, Inc., Independent Director at USG Corp., a Member at The Chicago Council on Global Affairs and a Member at The Conference Board, Inc. He is on the Board of Directors at Allison Transmission Holdings, Inc., ITT Corp., USG Corp., U.S.-India Business Council, U.S.-Korea Business Council, Bradley University and St. Mary of the Woods College. Mr. Lavin was previously employed as President, Chief Executive Officer & Director by Commercial Vehicle Group, Inc., Group President-Construction Industries & Growth by Caterpillar, Inc., Chairman by Caterpillar China Investment Co. Ltd., and Chairman by Shin Caterpillar Mitsubishi Ltd. He also served on the board at US-China Business Council. He received his undergraduate degree from Western Illinois University, a graduate degree from Creighton University and a graduate degree from Georgetown University.



